{"article_id":"QEUuwCfbM04Vk86m","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Romney 's team outraised President Obama 's by about $ 21 million last month .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"|","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Reuters photos |","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"REUTERS","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Romney winning the mega-donor war","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"Mitt Romney surged past President Barack Obama in May","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"fundraising on the shoulders of big donors","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"- an advantage","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the Republican nominee seems likely to sustain through November .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Romney and his super PAC allies and party team raised about $ 86 million in May ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"compared with roughly $ 65 million","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"raised by Obama and his allies ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"according to campaign finance reports","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"filed Wednesday .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"And Romney ' s not stopping there ;","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"his team is gearing up for an elaborate display of donor schmoozing this weekend ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"inviting 100 supporters","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"who have raised $ 100,000 or more","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to spend the weekend at a tony Utah ski resort with the former Massachusetts governor , his top campaign staff and GOP dignitaries such as Karl Rove and a host of prospective running mates ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"including Tim Pawlenty , Rob Portman , Paul Ryan and Bobby Jindal .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Obama ' s trying to keep up .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"While the president likes to cast his campaign as small-donor-powered ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Wednesday ' s reports show","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that his allies are mounting their own big-money push ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"landing a trio of new million-dollar donors to a supportive super PAC","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and raising bigger checks into a campaign committee","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"they quietly restructured","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"to allow larger donations .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"Taken together ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"the reports ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"filed with the Federal Election Commission ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"paint a picture of a Romney fundraising network","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"built for the new big-money age","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"that appears well positioned to challenge an Obama operation","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that in some ways is still struggling to adapt .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"\" It ' s easier to raise money in big chunks","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"if there are people","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"who are willing to give it that way ,","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"then it is to mobilize thousands of people","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"to give $ 20 each , \"","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"said Bob Biersack , a leading campaign finance tracker","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"who recently joined the Center for Responsive Politics after decades at the FEC .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"The mega donors ' impact has expanded this year ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"he said","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"\" because they ' re able to give to the candidates , as well as the parties and the joint committees ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and then give as much","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"as they want","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"to outside groups","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"that they know","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"are focused exclusively on helping that candidate . \"","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"Big donors had fueled gangbusters","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"fundraising for a collection of GOP super PACs ,","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"including the one","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"backing Romney ,","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"Restore Our Future ,","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"which pulled in $ 5 million ,","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"and Rove ' s American Crossroads ,","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"which pulled in $ 4.6 million ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"according to Wednesday filings .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Repeat donors to the super PACs included Pennsylvania medical executive Rocco Ortenzio , Idaho vitamin executive Frank VanderSloot and a company","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"controlled by Dallas developer","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"- and Romney fundraiser -","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"Harlan Crow .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"The three gave a combined $ 1.6 million last month .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"But Wednesday ' s reports don ' t fully reflect their efforts","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"to woo new donors","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"who previously wrote big checks to Romney ' s GOP opponents , such as casino mogul Sheldon Adelson ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"who pledged $ 10 million this month ,","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"and also has signaled","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"he intends to give big to American Crossroads ' s nonprofit sister group .","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"Democrats have been wringing their hands for months about their inability","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"to find an answer to Restore Our Future and a constellation of GOP-allied outside groups","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"already spending heavily on ads","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"attacking Obama .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"They got some good news Wednesday ,","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"when the pro-Obama super PAC Priorities USA Action ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"which had been struggling to woo big donors ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"reported pulling in $ 4 million in May","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"- its best month yet by far .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"That came largely thanks to three new donors","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"who gave $ 1 million each in May","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"- developer Franklin Haney , Houston lawyer Steve Mostyn and philanthropist Barbara Stiefel -","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"all of which had the group feeling good ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"and touting the impact of its ads","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"attacking Romney over his tenure at the helm of the private equity firm Bain Capital .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"But Priorities ' $ 18.6-million total haul for the cycle pales in comparison with the $ 61.5 million","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"raised by Restore Our Future .","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"Yet Wednesday ' s reports also illustrated","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"how the mega-donors ' significance increasingly reaches beyond the super PACs into the so-called hard money world of campaign committees .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":177,"left":92,"right":176,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":92,"left":0,"right":91,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":1,"right":90,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":157,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":4,"right":156,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":106,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":100,"right":105,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"left":95,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":93,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":97,"right":98,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":9,"right":96,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":96,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nucleari